item.media:description:
Este dibujo lo publique hace meses muy atrás en latinoamerica y para muchos dicen que motivo a algunos artistas en latinoamerica revolucionar sus dibujos a que sean muchas mucama francesas

En mi caso me pregunte a mi mismo

¿porque la cultura del fandom de FNaF no hace mas progresó para los human?
¿le hacen mas en animatronico que en humano?

¿Y sobre todo no muchos hacen (NSFW) O xxx a FNaF Human ? En cuanto lencería o algo similar a otra cosa

La mayoría del fandom dibuja lo mismo y sin repeticiones

Así que eso hice como quize dibujar a una French maid decidí dibujar a Mangle pole bear para empezar

Quería dibujar a chica pole bear pero dije. -no porque ella se ve como mucama solo que en vez de ser negros es amarillo en cuanto su traje-


Eso de la idea de dibujar mucamas francesas fue porque me obsesione viendo algunos anime y otros videos relacionados
pero bueno espero que les guste mi dibujo. Tarde 3 días en dibujarla creo que lo hice el mayo de 2018 creo

item.media:description:
Canon Morganites, while they have been mentioned in the SU canon, have not officially made their debut. As such, the design of my own Morganite is subject to change once Morganites are shown in a future SU episode. In the meantime, I have used the canon Emerald as a reference image for a possible Morganite look, so if the Morganite here looks similar to my own Emerald, you now know why.

Morganite is the Gem counterpart to Daniel.

The fancharacter depicted here belongs to Claudia Howard. For your sake, DO NOT repost, trace, copy, or steal this artwork.

Coral now has fins on her legs, inspired by retro Vaporeon and also has a darker blue color on her paws. They are shaped how a Sylveon has pink on its paws.

I added bubbles around her to make it look like she was underwater. Just got lazy and didn't color the background

✼ •• ┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈ •• ✼
Ability
HP: 5/5
PATK: 5/5
MATK: 4/5
Speed: Average/Fast
Attack Range: Medium/Long
Strength: Good with exploive attacks
Weakness: Bad with punching
Talent: Her Character System, Demolition Tactics, is similar to Chung’s Freiturnier but she can reload automatically
✼ •• ┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈ •• ✼
Backstory
Zetta is a mercenary from Lanox, She had been living on her own since her family was practically rich from all the explosives she sells. Her parents praised her for genius and let’s her live in her own house. Zetta enjoyed a carefree life despite living in the criminal underworld most of the time. She enjoyed sleeping, gazing at the sunset and sunrise as well as trees or passing clouds, and the taste of dumplings and soda. Occasionally she sometimes gaze on handsome men with glorious muscles but too shy to interact with them.

One night, when She turned fourteen, she was walking along and saw a gang of thugs harassing a family, the father was beaten to a pulp, the mother was being restrained and the kids were too scared to do anything. so Zetta felt obliged to interfere and took immediate action. She smacked one of the thugs with her Launcher then the rest started shooting at her, She quickly took cover but realized that she didn’t reload her Launcher so she had no choice but to use her prototype Plasma Grenades then blew the rest of the remaining thugs away with perfect accuracy. Zetta was captured by the police and given a sentence of fifteen to thirty years in prison. Though she nearly lost her life and only killed the men in self-defense to save a family from being murdered and possible enslavement , no one believed that she could use prototype explosives during a crossfire without getting injured, not to mention her using them showed her intention to kill the men. Luckily for her, there were witnesses around the time and they prove her innocence. Zetta was freed a week later, then went back to selling explosives, eventually she met the Legionnaires and now she serves as their explosive specialist.

✼ •• ┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈ •• ✼
Fun facts/Trivia
Her last name is based on the Spanish word for projectile

She has sthenolagnia, a fetish for muscular people.

Her clothes were originally gonna based on Rocket Raccon from Guardians of the Galaxy and Teemo from League of Legends

Especia is the Spanish word for spice

Bellona was an ancient Roman goddess of war. Her main attribute is the military helmet worn on her head; she often holds a sword, spear, or shield, and brandishes a torch or whip as she rides into battle in a four-horse chariot.

Energia Luminosa is a Spanish for light energy

✼ •• ┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈ •• ✼

One night, when She turned fourteen, she was walking along and saw a gang of thugs harassing a family, the father was beaten to a pulp, the mother was being restrained and the kids were too scared to do anything. so Zetta felt obliged to interfere and took immediate action. She smacked one of the thugs with her Launcher then the rest started shooting at her, She quickly took cover but realized that she didn’t reload her Launcher so she had no choice but to use her prototype Plasma Grenades then blew the rest of the remaining thugs away with perfect accuracy. Zetta was captured by the police and given a sentence of fifteen to thirty years in prison. Though she nearly lost her life and only killed the men in self-defense to save a family from being murdered and possible enslavement , no one believed that she could use prototype explosives during a crossfire without getting injured, not to mention her using them showed her intention to kill the men. Luckily for her, there were witnesses around the time and they prove her innocence. Zetta was freed a week later, then went back to selling explosives, eventually she met the Legionnaires and now she serves as their explosive specialist.

✼ •• ┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈ •• ✼
Fun facts/Trivia
Her last name is based on the Spanish word for projectile

She has sthenolagnia, a fetish for muscular people.

Her clothes were originally gonna based on Rocket Raccon from Guardians of the Galaxy and Teemo from League of Legends

Especia is the Spanish word for spice

Bellona was an ancient Roman goddess of war. Her main attribute is the military helmet worn on her head; she often holds a sword, spear, or shield, and brandishes a torch or whip as she rides into battle in a four-horse chariot.

Energia Luminosa is a Spanish for light energy
